# Tokenmaxxing Quest — Design Doc Rule

## Before making changes

Read [`docs/DESIGN.md`](../docs/DESIGN.md) before adding or changing gameplay mechanics, UI, architecture, or deployment.

For **gameplay, economy, pacing, upgrades, prestige, achievements, or progression copy**, also apply the **incremental-game-design** skill (`.cursor/skills/incremental-game-design/SKILL.md`). Run through its pre-implementation checklist before proposing or coding mechanic changes.

## After making changes

Update `docs/DESIGN.md` when you:

- Add, remove, or change a game mechanic
- Change architecture (modules, tick loop, save format)
- Add or modify hard requirements
- Ship a new version milestone

Always update the **Mechanics** table and **Changelog** section with a dated entry.

## Hard requirements (never violate)

- **Token-positive upgrades:** every purchasable upgrade must be framed as something that increases the number of tokens LLMs generate. No upgrade name or description may describe destroying, disposing, deprecating, wiping, blocking, or otherwise reducing tokens, models, prompts, or their data. Dark "purge" upgrades may be ruthless/ominous but must still drive token output upward. Endings/capstones are exempt (the purge capstone deliberately ends the run). Enforced by `test/upgrades.test.js`.
- HTML, CSS, and vanilla JS only — **no game engine** (Phaser, Pixi, Unity, etc.)
- Must run in a browser and work on mobile (touch targets, readable layout)
- Must remain deployable as static files on **GitHub Pages** (no required build step unless explicitly approved in DESIGN.md)
- Keep performance snappy: low-frequency tick loop, pause when tab hidden, minimal DOM writes

## Scope discipline

- Do not expand beyond the current version scope unless the user asks
- Put new ideas in DESIGN.md **Planned** section first, then implement in a focused follow-up
- Match satirical big-tech / tokenmaxxing tone in player-facing copy
- **Purchase buttons** use the label **Buy** for every token-cost upgrade (Agent Rule, Background Agent, model tier) — never alternate verbs like Certify or Upgrade on the button itself

## File map

```
index.html       — page shell
css/main.css     — styles
js/main.js       — boot + tick loop (composition root)
js/game.js       — Game engine (rules, tick, save/load)
js/state.js      — GameState data model + (de)serialization
js/clock.js      — Clock abstraction (System/Manual)
js/storage.js    — KeyValueStore abstraction (LocalStorage/Memory)
js/resources.js  — constants + formatting
js/ui.js         — DOM updates
test/            — headless unit tests (node --test)
docs/DESIGN.md   — source of truth (update this!)
```

## Testing

- Core logic must stay decoupled from the DOM so it is unit-testable headlessly.
- Inject `Clock`/`KeyValueStore` into `Game`; never call `Date.now()`/`localStorage` in engine code.
- Add/extend tests under `test/*.test.js` and run `node --test` (no build step, no deps).
